==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Candlefish
<hw>Can"dle*fish`</hw> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A marine fish (<spn>Thaleichthys Pacificus</spn>),
allied to the smelt, found on the north Pacific coast; -- called also
<altname>eulachon</altname>. It is so oily that, when dried, it may be
used as a candle, by drawing a wick through it</def>. <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The beshow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Candle foot</ent>⟦br⟧
